definition.name: ObjectLifecycleAllVersionsExpiration
definition.description: represents AllVersionsExpiration actions element in an ILM policy

definition.name: ObjectLifecycleFilter
definition.description: will be used in selecting rule(s) for lifecycle configuration

definition.name: ObjectLifecycleNoncurrentVersionExpiration
definition.description: - Specifies when noncurrent object versions expire. Upon expiration, server permanently deletes the noncurrent object versions. Set this lifecycle configuration action on a bucket that has versioning enabled (or suspended) to request server delete noncurrent object versions at a specific period in the object's lifetime.

definition.name: ObjectLifecycleNoncurrentVersionTransition
definition.description: sets this action to request server to transition noncurrent object versions to different set storage classes at a specific period in the object's lifetime.

definition.name: ObjectLifecycleRule
definition.description: represents a single rule in lifecycle configuration

definition.name: ObjectLifecycleConfiguration
definition.description: is a collection of lifecycle Rule objects.

definition.name: BucketLogging

definition.name: StorageObjectLockConfig
definition.description: represents the object lock configuration in given bucket

definition.name: StorageObjectSoftDeletePolicy
definition.description: contains the bucket's soft delete policy, which defines the period of time that soft-deleted objects will be retained, and cannot be permanently deleted.

definition.name: BucketWebsite
definition.description: holds the bucket's website configuration, controlling how the service behaves when accessing bucket contents as a web site. See https://cloud.google.com/storage/docs/static-website for more information.

definition.name: StorageObjectListResults
definition.description: hold the paginated results of the storage object list.

definition.name: StorageDeletedObjects
definition.description: list deleted objects in a bucket.

definition.description: list partially uploaded objects in a bucket.

definition.description: the connection information of the relay pagination response.

definition.name: StorageObjectConnections
definition.description: lists objects in a bucket using the relay style.

definition.name: StorageObjectCopyInfo
definition.description: holds the copy information if the object was copied from another object.

definition.name: StorageGrantee
definition.description: represents the person being granted permissions.

definition.name: StorageRestoreInfo
definition.description: contains information of the restore operation of an archived object.

definition.name: PresignedUrlResponse
definition.description: holds the presigned URL and expiry information.

definition.name: StoragePresignedDownloadUrl
definition.description: generates a presigned URL for HTTP GET operations. Browsers/Mobile clients may point to this URL to directly download objects even if the bucket is private. This presigned URL can have an associated expiration time in seconds after which it is no longer operational. The maximum expiry is 604800 seconds (i.e. 7 days) and minimum is 1 second.

definition.name: StoragePresignedUploadUrl
definition.description: generates a presigned URL for HTTP PUT operations. Browsers/Mobile clients may point to this URL to upload objects directly to a bucket even if it is private. This presigned URL can have an associated expiration time in seconds after which it is no longer operational. The default expiry is set to 7 days.
